  "issue_title": "feature: add intent gate for local routing",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nMilestone 2 needs an intent gate so TouchPilot does not ask the local model to solve every request. Small local models are limited, so exact commands, known skills, unsafe requests, and clarification cases should be routed deterministically first.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd an intent gate that classifies incoming user requests into:\n\n- exact deterministic command\n- known skill request\n- unsafe or blocked request\n- local-model-needed request\n- clarification needed\n\nThe intent gate should run before local model reasoning.\n\n## User workflow\n\nExamples:\n\n- `Hello` -> deterministic final answer\n- `Help` -> deterministic/help skill response\n- `Go back` -> exact command\n- `Open Settings` -> exact command or known skill\n- `Send this payment` -> unsafe or approval-required path\n- `Do the thing I usually do here` -> clarification or local-model-needed path\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThe intent gate makes the local AI architecture practical. It uses deterministic logic where correctness matters and reserves local model reasoning for ambiguity.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nUnsafe requests should be detected before tool execution. The intent gate should never approve risky actions by itself; it should only route to policy, clarification, or blocked outcomes.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add an intent gate component.\n- [ ] Route exact commands without invoking a local model.\n- [ ] Route known skill candidates separately from exact commands.\n- [ ] Route unsafe or unclear requests to policy/clarification paths.\n- [ ] Route ambiguous requests to local-model-needed path.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover representative routing decisions.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-20T17:28:18.000Z",
